bdf2sfd
------------------------------------------
bdf2sfd is a BDF to SFD converter, allowing to vectorize bitmap fonts. It works
by converting each pixel of a glyph to a polygon, which produces large and
unoptimized SFD files that should be post-processed using FontForge.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.4.6-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.40-1
  cmake-3.23.2-1
  cygport-0.36.4-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  ninja-1.11.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/fcambus/bdf2sfd

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/fcambus/bdf2sfd/archive/refs/tags/1.1.8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack bdf2sfd-1.1.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./bdf2sfd-1.1.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/bdf2sfd-1.1.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/bdf2sfd-1.1.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(bdf2sfd)
  /usr/bin/bdf2sfd.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/bdf2sfd.README
  /usr/share/doc/bdf2sfd/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/bdf2sfd/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/bdf2sfd/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/bdf2sfd/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/bdf2sfd/THANKS
  /usr/share/man/man1/bdf2sfd.1.gz

